Title: A Winning Strategy for Roulette  
Author: Jerome H. Klotz 
Keyword: Key words and phrases: Roulette, Bayes strategy, Dirichlet prior, convex loss, expected log return.  
Address: Madison  
Affiliation: University of Wisconsin at  
Abstract: We examine the statistical problem of computing a favorable betting strategy for the game of roulette with an unbalanced wheel. Using negative average expected log capital after n plays for loss function, we show that the Bayes strategy for a Dirichlet prior is asymptotically optimal. We simulate to illustrate the behavior of the strategy for a biased favorable wheel and an unbiased unfavorable wheel.
